        <updateDate>2021-05-04T14:29:04Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Save Oak Flat Act</b></p> <p>This bill repeals the requirement for the Department of Agriculture to convey the 2,422 acres of Forest Service land located in Tonto National Forest in Pinal County, Arizona,&nbsp;known as Oak Flat, to Resolution Copper Mining, LLC, in exchange&nbsp;for various parcels of land owned by Resolution Copper. </p> <p>Oak Flat is withdrawn from (1) entry, appropriation, or disposal under the public land laws; (2) location, entry, and patent under the mining laws; and (3) disposition under all laws pertaining to mineral and geothermal leasing or mineral materials.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
